Subject: RE: [T2] Adding and Converting AC Systems

I don't have experience with the converting of an a/c system to use the new
Sanden stuff, but I did read the article. I checked out the websites named
and emailed them. I cannot remember what website it was, but they are in the
process of making a complete custom a/c system for the bay window busses.
They said it will be ready in a few months. This system uses Sanden 508
compressor and will have all brackets. They also sell the stuff separately.
You may want to email them and find out if they have the brackets you need.
The website was the last one in the article. I do not have the mag here
right now, but if you find the website address, send it to the list. I think
it was Gilmore Enterprises or something like that. The author of the article
made it sound like the best deal and I think it may be. The only catch is
that some of their systems for split window busses cost about $1200. A
little high for a/c.

Corbett

